ng indemnity agreement shall not inure to the benefit of any Initial Purchaser from whom the person asserting any loss, claim, damage, liability or expense purchased Notes, or any person controlling such Initial Purchaser, if copies of the Final Offering Memorandum were timely delivered to the Initial Purchaser pursuant to Section 2 and a copy of the Final Offering Memorandum (as then amended or supplemented if the Company shall have furnished any amendments or supplements thereto) was not sent or given by or on behalf of such Initial Purchaser to such person, if required by law so to have been delivered, at or prior to the written confirmation of the sale of the Notes to such person, and if the Final Offering
