Notwithstanding anything in this Agreement to the contrary, the Buyer agrees (on behalf of itself and each other Buyer Party) with the Seller (for the benefit of the Seller and each other Seller) that the provisions of this Schedule 6 shall operate to limit the liability of the Sellers in respect of any claim arising under any Transaction Document (including in respect of any of the Seller Warranties) or otherwise, whether in tort, contract, under statute or otherwise.
The provisions of this Schedule 6 shall not apply to any claim under any of the Seller Warranties or otherwise under a Transaction Document that arises as a result of fraud by any Seller.
 
