Warrants
In 2008, 110 common stock warrants were issued to the subordinated debt holders in exchange for their forgiveness of accrued default interest. The warrants could be exercised for 10% of the common stock in the Company for $.01 per share. The warrants were valued in 2008 at $415.84 each based on an option pricing valuation model and were adjusted to fair value each balance sheet date. The warrants were recorded as a liability in the balance sheet in the amount of $46 as of December 31, 2010, and were terminated in connection with the Restructuring on May 5, 2011.
